Content:: Guillaume Van Keirsbulck (born 14 February 1991) is a Belgian professional road bicycle racer, who currently rides for UCI ProTeam Alpecin–Deceuninck.[4] Born in Roeselare, Van Keirsbulck is the grandson of Benoni Beheyt and got his first major win in 2011 when winning the Omloop van het Houtland.[5] In June 2017, he was named in the startlist for the 2017 Tour de France.[6]
